Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Phase 5: executor resolves conductor nodes from the
 workspace store
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes the loudest Phase 3 caveat: today executor.ts runs the STATIC node
definitions in nodes.ts, so optimizer promotions (updateNodePrompt) and authoring
edits are live for independent execution and replay but never reach full
Publishing-Conductor runs.

The executor now resolves its node list through resolveConductorNodes(), gated by
WORKSPACE_NODES_SOURCE=static|store and defaulting to static (behavior unchanged
until an operator flips it). In store mode each canonical node is overlaid with its
stored counterpart, so promoted prompts, schemas, tools, skills, and model config
reach the conductor.

Canonical-node guard: the DAG topology (id, dependsOn, produces), grid position,
node status, and the publish-risk classification (riskLevel) stay pinned to the
static definition regardless of store contents — a store edit changes how a node
runs, never the shape of the conductor graph or a publish gate. A canonical node
missing from the store is seeded from static (late-stage seeding preserved); a
store-read failure falls back to static so a transient repository error never
aborts a run.

Tests: tests/agent/workspaceNodeSource.test.ts (8 cases) — default static,
prompt overlay, topology/publish-risk guard, missing-node seeding, read-failure
fallback, and an end-to-end proof that a promoted prompt reaches a mock conductor
run while static mode ignores it. Full suite 583 passing, typecheck clean.

