Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Phase 7: enforce the model ladder in the conductor
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The cost-aware model ladder (recommendModel) was advisory only — surfaced via
optimizer.status but never applied. This wires enforcement: enforceModelLadder()
applies the cheapest model whose rubric pass-rate clears the threshold (over at
least minSamples evaluated outputs) to the node about to run, at conductor dispatch.

Gated by IMPROVEMENT_MODEL_LADDER_ENFORCE (default OFF, so the ladder stays advisory
unless an operator opts in), tunable via IMPROVEMENT_MODEL_LADDER_THRESHOLD /
IMPROVEMENT_MODEL_LADDER_MIN_SAMPLES. It is downshift-only and eval-gated, and a
per-run override rather than a workspace mutation — persisting a model choice stays
the human-approved optimizer.promote path, so disabling the flag fully reverts. Builds
directly on Phase 5's store-node modelConfig overlay. Enforcement is best-effort: an
eval-repository error leaves the node on its configured model and never fails a run.

Also refreshes the optimizer.ts scope note now that Phase 5 landed.

Tests: tests/agent/modelLadderEnforcement.test.ts (7 cases) — cheapest-qualified
selection (skips a cheaper failing model), no-op when already on the recommended
model, insufficient-samples guard, threshold override, flag parsing, and an
end-to-end proof the conductor tags the dispatched node in mock mode with the flag on
and stays untouched with it off. Full suite 590 passing, typecheck clean.

